cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SI

This paper discusses the detection and classification of malicious software through dynamic analysis using sandboxing techniques. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since machine learning techniques are often used in dynamic analysis. The paper also discusses benchmarking the efficiency of different sandbox systems, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the use of agent-based and agentless systems could also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves the interaction and communication between different components of the system.
